The paper proposes a novel optimization method for network community partitioning based on network structure information. This falls under the category of network science and social network analysis, which is closely related to topics such as machine learning, data mining, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces a new centrality measure and utilizes convex optimization algorithms, which are common in machine learning and optimization research, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which are relevant to cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
